{"id":"kareah","term":"Kareah","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Bald, the father of Johanan and Jonathan, who for a time were loyal to Gedaliah, the Babylonian governor of Jerusalem (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 40:8\">Jer. 40:8</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 40:13\">13</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 40:15\">15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 40:16\">16</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Jeremiah 40:8","Jeremiah 40:13","Jeremiah 40:15","Jeremiah 40:16"]}